<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,152,299]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
This may be the first record for this tribe in 
<collectingCountry box="[648,770,186,207]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
, though Bowring wrote in a letter dated 
<date box="[1183,1323,182,207]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="1851-06-02">
<number box="[1183,1196,185,207]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="2.0">2</number>
nd June 
<number box="[1270,1323,185,207]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="1851.0">1851</number>
</date>
, that in the spring he had caught &quot;one or two species like 
<taxonomicName authority="Anon, 1851" authorityName="Anon" authorityYear="1851" box="[613,702,217,238]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[613,702,217,238]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Pogonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (Anon, 
<number box="[795,847,215,237]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="1851.0">1851</number>
) presumably from 
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1162,216,237]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
. The imago is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Marsham 1802" authorityName="Marsham" authorityYear="1802" box="[181,485,246,268]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalceus">
<emphasis box="[181,299,246,268]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">P. chalceus</emphasis>
(Marsham 
<number box="[424,478,246,268]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="1802.0">1802</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but with paler legs, antennae and apical quarter of elytra. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1124,1218,246,268]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Material</emphasis>
: Æ‹ W.T.L., 
<date box="[1352,1432,246,268]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="2015-07-06">
<number box="[1352,1366,246,268]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="6.0">6</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[1405,1432,246,268]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="15.0">15</number>
</date>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,233,277,299]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Biology</emphasis>
: Imago found July. Can be attracted to light. It seems to prefer vertical surfaces on which it was quite agile.
</paragraph>
